  <div class="section" id="tools">
    <h3>Tools for Unlearning</h3>
    <p>Want better answers? Ask more dangerous questions. These tools aren’t here to optimise your funnel—they’re here to unpick it.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong><a href="#" title="Coming soon – assess how much of your strategy is just brand doctrine on autopilot.">Brand Conformity Score</a>:</strong> A diagnostic to assess how deeply your strategy clings to branding orthodoxy. Based on how you think, not just what you say.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="#bias-cards" title="Interactive flip cards – inspired by Kahneman, Tversky, and post-rational insight work.">Bias Breaker Cards</a>:</strong> Reveal the cognitive traps behind your decisions—powered by behavioural economics. Designed for 1:1s or workshop chaos.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="#" title="Print-at-home provocations to help you dismantle and rebuild your brand thinking.">Unbrand Your Brand Worksheets</a>:</strong> A downloadable workbook that pushes you to strip back, simplify, and question everything. No fluff. Just hard thinking in plain English.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="bias-cards">
    <h3>Bias Breaker Cards</h3>
    <p>Click a card to flip it and challenge how you think. Use them in strategy reviews, brand workshops, or on your own when you’re about to bluff something into a deck.</p>
    <div class="card-grid">
      <div class="card" onclick="this.classList.toggle('flipped')">
        <div class="card-inner">
          <div class="card-front"><strong>Confirmation Bias</strong><br>You only see what fits.</div>
          <div class="card-back">What would disprove your theory? Go find it.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" onclick="this.classList.toggle('flipped')">
        <div class="card-inner">
          <div class="card-front"><strong>Groupthink</strong><br>You agree too easily.</div>
          <div class="card-back">Ask: What’s the worst if we’re wrong?</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" onclick="this.classList.toggle('flipped')">
        <div class="card-inner">
          <div class="card-front"><strong>Authority Bias</strong><br>You defer to power.</div>
          <div class="card-back">Remove names. Test anonymously.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" onclick="this.classList.toggle('flipped')">
        <div class="card-inner">
          <div class="card-front"><strong>Recency Bias</strong><br>You overvalue what's recent.</div>
          <div class="card-back">What stayed true for a decade?</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" onclick="this.classList.toggle('flipped')">
        <div class="card-inner">
          <div class="card-front"><strong>Loss Aversion</strong><br>You fear risk too much.</div>
          <div class="card-back">What if you had nothing left to lose?</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" onclick="this.classList.toggle('flipped')">
        <div class="card-inner">
          <div class="card-front"><strong>Sunk Cost Fallacy</strong><br>You can’t let go.</div>
          <div class="card-back">Would you back it if it came in today?</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" onclick="this.classList.toggle('flipped')">
        <div class="card-inner">
          <div class="card-front"><strong>Halo Effect</strong><br>You blur the good bits.</div>
          <div class="card-back">List what works. List what doesn’t. Separate them.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" onclick="this.classList.toggle('flipped')">
        <div class="card-inner">
          <div class="card-front"><strong>False Consensus</strong><br>You assume everyone agrees.</div>
          <div class="card-back">Who’s “everyone”? Get data. Or say nothing.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" onclick="this.classList.toggle('flipped')">
        <div class="card-inner">
          <div class="card-front"><strong>Narrative Fallacy</strong><br>You force a story.</div>
          <div class="card-back">What if your founder’s story is irrelevant?</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" onclick="this.classList.toggle('flipped')">
        <div class="card-inner">
          <div class="card-front"><strong>Status Quo Bias</strong><br>You do what’s always been done.</div>
          <div class="card-back">Who broke the pattern and survived?</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
